{#- ### Top Findings — HTML table with rowspan on Component column. -#}
{#- Inputs: rows [{rank, criticality, path_glyph, path_anchor, finding_id, finding_title, component_id, component_name, comp_rowspan, mitigations[{id,action,priority}]}], total_qualifying. -#}
{#- comp_rowspan: >0 = start of run (emit <td rowspan=N>), 0 = continuation (skip cell). -#}
### Top Findings

**{{ rows | length }} highest-risk items.** Full catalogue in [§8 Threat Register](#8-threat-register). **Pfad** links to the attack path in [Security Posture at a Glance](#security-posture-at-a-glance); mitigation IDs jump to [§9](#9-mitigation-register).

<table>
<thead>
<tr><th>#</th><th>Criticality</th><th>Pfad</th><th>Finding</th><th>Component</th><th>Primary Mitigations</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
{%- for r in rows %}
<tr>
  <td>{{ r.rank }}</td>
  <td>{{ severity_emoji(r.criticality) }} {{ severity_label(r.criticality) }}</td>
  <td>{% if r.path_glyph %}[{{ r.path_glyph }}](#{{ r.path_anchor }}){% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
  <td>[{{ r.finding_id }}](#{{ r.finding_id | lower }}) — {{ r.finding_title }}</td>
  {%- if r.comp_rowspan > 0 %}
  <td rowspan="{{ r.comp_rowspan }}">[{{ r.component_id }}](#{{ r.component_id | lower }}) — {{ r.component_name }}</td>
  {%- endif %}
  <td>{{ r.mitigations | format_mitigations }}</td>
</tr>
{%- endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>

{% if total_qualifying > (rows | length) -%}
_+{{ total_qualifying - (rows | length) }} additional ≥High findings — see [§8 Threat Register](#8-threat-register)._
{% endif %}
_Legend: 🔴 Critical (directly exploitable, major impact) · 🟠 High. **Pfad** glyphs ①–⑦ link back to the matching bullet in [Security Posture at a Glance](#security-posture-at-a-glance)._
